ew Haven: Yale University Press.Held, David, 1996. Models of Democracy. Cambridge Polity Press.Huntington, Samuel P., 1984. The Third Wave: Democratization in the Late Twentieth Century. Norman and London: University of Oklahoma Press.Lijphart, Arend, 1984. Democracies. Patterns of Majoritarian and Consensus Government in Twenty-One Countries. New Haven:Yale University Press.Linz, Juan J. and Alfred Stepan, 1996. Problems of Democratic Transition and Consolidation：Southern Europe, South America and Post-Communist Europe. Baltimore：Johns Hopkins University Press.Lipset, S. M. 1960. "Some Social Requisites of Democracy: Economic Development and PoliticalLegitimacy". American Political Science Review, No. 53 , pp. 69-105.Przeworski, A., M. Alvarez, Jos'' A. Cheibub and F. Limongi, l996. “What  Makes Democracies Endure？” Journal of Democracy, Vol.7(No.1):pp.39-55.Sartori, Giovanni, 1987. The Theory of Democracy Revisited. New Jersey:  Chatham House Publishers.Sorensen, Georg, 1998. Democracy and Democratization: Processes and  Prospects in a Changing World. 2nd ed., Oxford: Westview Press.
